Defendant Ariel A Halverson in court with attorney Samuel W. Benedict.  Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a no contest plea to count 1 and count 2 is dismissed and read-in. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was given the following:

WITHHELD SENTENCE;

TERM OF PROBATION:   18 months

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  

*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
 *Not to operate a motor vehicle unless licensed
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

*Six months driver's license revocation

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME: 45 DAYS, STAYED; to be used at agent's discretion.  Agent to determine with or without non working hours.  (2 days credit)

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
